<doc id="45018" wikidata="Q1994017" url="?curid=45018" title="1250s BC">
<text>The 1250s BC is a decade which lasted from 1259 BC to 1250 BC.

==Events and trends==
*‚ÄîRamesses II makes a peace agreement with the Hittites (other date is 1263 BC).
*‚ÄîThe Exodus as depicted in the Bible.
*1251 BC‚ÄîSeptember 7, a solar eclipse on this date might mark the birth of legendary Heracles at Thebes, Greece.
*1250 BC‚ÄîTraditional date of the beginning of the Trojan War.
*‚ÄîWu Ding, king of the Shang dynasty, and earliest archaeologically confirmed Chinese monarch begins his reign.
*‚ÄîEarliest surviving writing from Ancient China. 
*‚ÄîChariots appear in Ancient China.
*‚ÄîLion Gate, Mycenae, Greece, are made. Citadel walls are built.
*‚ÄîPapyrus of Ani created, during the 19th dynasty of the New Kingdom of Egypt.
*‚ÄîTawagalawa letter sent from a Hittite king to a king of the Ahhiyawa

==Significant people==
* Wu Ding, king of the Shang dynasty.
* Sanchuniathon, Phoenician writer, is born (approximate date).

==Fiction==
* S.M. Stirling&#x27;s Nantucket series is set in Bronze Age era, circa the 1250s BC.

