*Monbazillac
*Manoir de Gr√©zignac
*Manoir de la Vermondie
*Manoir des Pautis
*P√©cany
*Puymartin
*Saulnier

The famous caves of Lascaux have been closed to the public, but a replica of Lascaux II is open to visitors and is a major tourist attraction. P√©rigueux has important Roman ruins, including an arena which is still visible inside a public park located near the town centre.

Dordogne is particularly popular with Britons as well as people from a variety of other countries, as a location for second homes.

